value:
On the title page the date of publication appears preceding the printer information.
Engraved title page devices. With half-title pages.
Illustrations: 96 full-page etchings, by G.B. Piranesi (20, 19 signed), N. Mogalli (21 signed or initialed), F.P. Duflos (8 signed) and others; Piranesi's and some others repeated from his Raccolte di varie vedute di Roma (Roma, 1752), the previous edition of which was published as Varie vedute di Roma (Roma, 1748). Cf. Hind, A.M. Piranesi, p. 76-78. Large map on folded leaf by N. Mogalli and G. Petroschi; title page vignette; small cut, v.1, p. vi; 3 head- and tailpieces; 2 pictorial initials.
Colophon of vol. 2: Typis Reverendae Camerae Apostolicae.
Index in vol. 2. With list of subscribers in vol. 2.
Old classmark: 578.R6.
Binding: tree calf, border (double g. fillet); spine & board edges g.t., border g.t. on inside covers, g. lettering; marbled e.p.; a.e. yellow.
